The US government on Friday pledged Sh103 million to the Ministry of Environment and the Africa Conservation Centre to support Kenya&rsquo;s National Wildlife Conservation Strategy.The grant will support conservation and efforts to combat wildlife crime in Kenya and East Africa.It and seven other grants awarded over the past year were given through the US Agency for International Development and Department of the Interior.This came as the world marked World Wildlife Day on Friday.Speaking at the Nairobi Animal Orphanage, US Ambassador Robert Godec said, &ldquo;By protecting wildlife and the environment, we can create jobs and build prosperity while preserving Kenya&rsquo;s rich natural heritage.&rdquo;